14 WHEREAS, U.S. Route 66, also known as the “Mother Road”, was
15 established in 1926 and served as a vital artery of American
16 transportation, running from Chicago, Illinois, to Santa Monica,
17 California, with over 400 miles traversing the State of Oklahoma;
18 and
19 WHEREAS, Route 66 played a pivotal role in the migration west
20 during the Dust Bowl era, providing a path to opportunity and
21 survival for countless Oklahomans; and
22 WHEREAS, the communities along Route 66 in Oklahoma have long
23 served as vibrant centers of commerce, culture, and hospitality,
